.TH "SPEECHRECOGNITION.INTERIMRESULTS" "3JS" "September 30, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SpeechRecognition.interimResults \- SpeechRecognition: interimResults
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]interimResults\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]SpeechRecognition\f[R] interface controls whether interim results
should be returned (\f[CR]true\f[R]) or not (\f[CR]false\f[R]).
Interim results are results that are not yet final (e.g., the
\f[CR]SpeechRecognitionResult.isFinal\f[R] property is
\f[CR]false\f[R]).
.PP
The default value for \f[B]\f[CB]interimResults\f[B]\f[R] is
\f[CR]false\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A boolean value representing the state of the current
\f[CR]SpeechRecognition\f[R]\(cqs interim results.
\f[CR]true\f[R] means interim results are returned, and \f[CR]false\f[R]
means they aren\(cqt.
.SH EXAMPLES
This code is excerpted from our \c
.UR https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/blob/main/web-speech-api/speech-color-changer/script.js
Speech color changer
.UE \c
\ example.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] recognition = \f[B]new\f[R] SpeechRecognition();
recognition.lang = \(dqen\-US\(dq;
recognition.interimResults = \f[B]false\f[R];
recognition.maxAlternatives = 1;

\f[I]// \&...\f[R]
.EE
